Package io.xmljim.algorithms.model.util

Class Scalar

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Number
io.xmljim.algorithms.model.util.Scalar
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Scalar>
public final class Scalar
extends Number
implements Comparable<Scalar>
A scalar represents any value that can be interpreted as a number. Internally, the class can transform specific types into numeric representations e.g., dates (LocalDate), date-times (LocalDateTime, booleans. classes that are subclasses of Number are stored without transformation.
